1️⃣ Get the output element
const output = document.getElementById('output');
document.getElementById('output') finds the HTML element with the ID output.
This is where we will show the result (point of sail and advice).
We store it in a variable output so we can easily change its content.
2️⃣ Set the basic HTML content
output.innerHTML = "<strong>Point of Sail:</strong> " + data.point + "<br><strong>Advice:</strong>";
data.point comes from Flask (pos.py) and is the point of sail.
innerHTML allows us to insert HTML instead of plain text.
<strong> makes the text bold.
<br> inserts a line break.

At this point, the webpage will show something like:

Point of Sail: Close Haul
Advice:
3️⃣ Create a <ul> element
const ul = document.createElement("ul");
This creates a new unordered list element (<ul>).
It is currently empty — we will fill it with <li> items next.
4️⃣ Loop through the advice array
data.advice.forEach(item => {
    const li = document.createElement("li");
    li.textContent = item;
    ul.appendChild(li);
});
data.advice is an array of strings from Flask (your advice lines).
.forEach(item => { ... }) loops through each advice string.
For each item:
document.createElement("li") creates a new list item (<li>).
li.textContent = item sets the text of that list item to your advice.
ul.appendChild(li) adds the list item to the <ul> element.

After this loop, your <ul> contains one <li> for each advice line.

5️⃣ Add the <ul> to the page
output.appendChild(ul);
Finally, we attach the <ul> (with all the <li> items) to the output element.
The page now shows the advice as a bullet-point list under “Advice:”

Example output:

Point of Sail: Close Haul
Advice:

Keep sails tight
Crew forward and ready to move to balance the boat
Skipper forward on the side opposite the mainsail
Keep 15°-20° heel
Centerboard fully down
Adjust outhaul